      <title xml:lang="en">IGCH 721</title>
      <noteSet>
         <note>The BCH report mentions a hoard of 12 (?)  AV dr. found on Thasos: from which Athens acquired. one piece. Another 8 AV dr., at Thessalonica, are said to have been found in the 1960's at Stryme. The BM has casts of additional dr. appearing on the market at about the same time. Some of the pieces are of doubtful authenticity. It seems likely that all of the material pertains to the same find but the number of genuine coins, as well as the date and place of discovery, cannot be established</note>
